Last Broadcast Date: Sun 9 May 2010
Forging Links American political scientist Professor Charles Kupchan explains why no conflict need be eternal and lays out his recipe for peace making. Jordanian artist Samah Hijawi shares her experience of reaching out to the people of Amman, through sounds, pictures and speeches. And award winning author Joan Brady charts her artistic journey from ballet dancer to writer and what role the spectator and reader plays in all of this. Changing the tune to turn literary or balletic enemies into friends in a public place by Emily Kasriel Show less